  "prompt": "What is a vitamin?",
  "response": "A vitamin is an organic compound that is essential for normal growth and nutrition in living organisms. Here are some key points about vitamins:\n\n1. They are micronutrients needed in small quantities\n2. The body cannot produce most vitamins, so they must be obtained through diet\n3. They play crucial roles in metabolism, immune function, and other bodily processes\n4. Vitamins are typically classified as either fat-soluble (A, D, E, K) or water-soluble (B vitamins and C)\n5. Different vitamins have different functions, such as supporting bone health, vision, energy production, and cell growth\n6. Vitamin deficiencies can lead to various health problems and diseases\n\nHumans need 13 essential vitamins to maintain good health, which can be found in foods like fruits, vegetables, meats, and dairy products.",
